while (next operator or operand is not end-of-file indicator)
	if (number)
		push it
	else if (operator)
		pop number
		do operation
		push result
	else if (newline)
		pop and print top of stack
	else 
		error

Exercise 4-3. Given the basic framework, it's straightforward to extend the 
calculator. Add the modulus (%) operator and provisions for negative numbers.
Outline: 
1. add the modulus (%) operator: 
while (next operator or operand is not end-of-file indicator)
	... ...
	else if (%)
		pop number
		do modulus operation
		push result
	... ...
2. provisions for negative numbers
getop {
	... ...
	if (not a minus)
		return
	else if (c = getch() is not a integer) {
		return
}
	else {;}
	......
}
